    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Irving Penn<br />
American, 1917–2009<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>Arshile Gorky &amp; Wifredo Lam (B), New York</em>, July 17, 1946, printed January 26, 1999</h3>

    <p>
    Gelatin silver print, edition of 11<br />    24.2 x 19.4 cm (image); 25.1 x 20.2 cm (paper)<br />    Stamped and inscribed verso, upper left, in black ink: “REF. 18454,” inscribed verso, upper center, in black ink: “.. / ARSHILE GORKY AND WILFREDO LAM B [in a circle] / (NEW YORK, JULY 17, 1946) [in a box]”; stamped and inscribed verso, center, in black ink: “PHOTOGRAPH BY IRVING PENN / Copyright (c) 1999 by Irving Penn / Courtesy of Vogue / Not to be reproduced without / written permission of / photographer.”; signed, stamped, and inscribed verso, lower left, in black ink: “Irving Penn / IRVING PENN [in a circle] / Print made Jan. 26, 1999. / I.P.”; stamped and inscribed verso, center right, in black ink: “SIGNED PRINTS OF THIS PHOTOGRAPH / NOT EXCEEDING 11. / I.P.”; stamped verso, lower center, in black ink: “TONED IN: SELENIUM”; stamped verso, lower center, in black ink: “HYPO ELIMINATED.”<br />    Gift of Irving Penn, 2001.96</p>
        Copyright The Irving Penn Foundation
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

  </div>
  <!--/artwork-details-->

    
      <div id="artwork-body">
                <div id="abbrev">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/more" class="more">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
      <!--content hidden-->
    </div>
    <div id="extended">
      <p><a href="http://www.artic.edu//aic/collections/exhibitions/IrvingPennArchives/artwork/less" class="less">Exhibition, Publication and Ownership Histories</a></p>
            <h2>Exhibition History</h2>
      <p>London, England, National Portrait Gallery, "Irving Penn Portraits," February 18–May 30, 2010; traveled to the Palazzo delle Esposizioni, Rome, July 1-September 19, 2010. (Magda Keaney)</p>
                  <h2>Publication History</h2>
      <p>Westerbeck, Colin. 1997. “Irving Penn: A Career in Photography.” Exh. cat. Art Institute of Chicago/Bulfinch Press. p. 136, fig. 7. (other print of this image/variant showing different pose)</p>
                  <h2>Ownership History</h2>
      <p>Given by the artist to the Art Institute, 2001.</p>
